gujarati.context:
Beautifully is it glorious this world of God's, entered by Jiva's dharma; 
Thankful thankful be Thou, O Savior, in that way; 
Thankful is the devotee, grateful to Thee, O Savior, having crossed over with devotion;

Here is the translation:

In their nest, birds chirp with empty shells, singing; 
Many trees are shaken where village songs are, I know the second name of this dharma's path.

Here is the translation:

There is beauty in the world, it shines like a city without limit; 
The twice-born, the noble, and the merchant have fallen to the level of the lowly, out of grief for their religion, like an ocean.

Here is the translation:

Truthful one is extremely sense-driven, dear; patient and humble in true faith, dear; 
Morally good, satisfied, generous, dear; auspicious peace, treasure of virtues, dear.

Here is the translation:

Such a childlike person, great in wisdom, says that one who has good luck surrounding him/her; 
He/She has taken oath of virtues and has become chaste; having divine duty free, she is an unblemished maiden.

Here is the translation:

Heye het samet hulave re, premay paranyaam maan julaave re;
Kare kaam dhaamanu jo kani re, pan vritt rahay baalak maan re.

Here is the translation:

"Rude happiness takes away one's sleep, just like sugar gets packed; 
When they do great things, then my mouth becomes busy speaking."

This is what it says:

It's seen by the young and old, this father is great; known as a big yogi are you; 

From birth eight years go by, just like that, settled at home stay you.
